:INFO
Ollama Setup on Mac
Step-by-step guide for getting Ollama running on an Apple Silicon or Intel Mac with a writing-optimized model.

:TASK
[ ] Download Ollama from ollama.com
[ ] Run the installer and open Terminal
[ ] Run: ollama pull mistral
[ ] Start a session: ollama run mistral
[ ] Create a Modelfile with your system prompt
[ ] Build a named model: ollama create writer-v1 -f Modelfile
[ ] Run your custom model: ollama run writer-v1

:NOTE
The Modelfile FORMAT line sets the base model. The SYSTEM block defines the assistant persona. Keep your system prompt under 500 words for best performance on smaller models.

:LINK
https://ollama.com
Ollama: run large language models locally